    <mads:note type="source">"Apollonides, 3, from Smyrna?, epigrammatic poet, writer of epigrams who
      lived around the beginning of the Christian era (cf. Anth. Pal. 9,280; 287; 791; 10,19);
      author of 29 poems from the 'Garland' of Philippus (9,264; 408 cannon be attributed with
      certainty; 16,235 however, is credited to the otherwise unknown Apollonius of Smyrna); for the
      major part epideictic and funerary epigrams....." .Degani, Enzo (Bologna); "Apollonides."
      Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill,
      2007. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 02 August 2007</mads:note>
    <mads:note type="source"/>
